The paper presents a method for planning robust grasps over uncertain shape completed objects using a deep neural network with dropout layers for shape completion and Monte Carlo sampling. The focus is on robotics and manipulation tasks, which suggests the cs.RO (Robotics) category. The use of a deep neural network for shape completion and Monte Carlo sampling suggests the cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. The evaluation of the method's performance and comparison with another state-of-the-art method suggests the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the application of the method to complex or unknown objects suggests the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category.
